\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 CONFIDENCE ENGINE v1.0\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf0 Confidence should answer:\
\'93How safe is this decision relative to alternatives?\'94\
It is NOT:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\ls46\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
How good the player is\
\ls46\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
How high the projection is\
\ls46\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
How much you like him\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 It is:\
Score Separation adjusted for Risk\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 Step 1: Core Variables\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf0 For a start/sit decision between Player A and Player B:\
We already have:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f6\fs26 \cf0 \
\
score_A\
score_B\
volatility_A\
volatility_B\
role_risk_A\
role_risk_B\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 We compute:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f6\fs26 \cf0 \
\
score_gap = score_A - score_B\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 Absolute gap determines base certainty.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 Step 2: Base Confidence (Gap Driven)\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf0 We convert gap into a percentage.\
Use this structure:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f6\fs26 \cf0 \
\
base_confidence = min(95, 50 + (score_gap * 5))\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 Meaning:\
Gap = 0 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f2  50%\uc0\u8232 Gap = 2 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f2  60%\uc0\u8232 Gap = 4 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f2  70%\uc0\u8232 Gap = 6 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f2  80%\uc0\u8232 Gap = 9 
\f4 \uc0\u8594 
\f2  95% (capped)\
This makes intuitive sense.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs36 \cf0 Step 3: Risk Adjustment Layer\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf0 Now we adjust for volatility and role instability.\
First compute combined risk:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f6\fs26 \cf0 \
\
combined_volatility = (volatility_A + volatility_B) / 2\
combined_role_risk = (role_risk_A + role_risk_B) / 2\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 Now apply penalty:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f6\fs26 \cf0 \
\
risk_penalty = combined_volatility * 10\
role_penalty = (1 - combined_role_risk) * 10\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 Then:\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f6\fs26 \cf0 \
\
confidence = base_confidence - risk_penalty - role_penalty\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs24 \cf0 Clamp between 50\'9695%.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

